cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.SE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it discusses a control plane abstraction for CPU-bound cloud applications. It may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it discusses scheduling decisions and partitioning of work. Additionally, it could be categorized under Databases (cs.DB) as it discusses large scale data analytics applications. Machine learning is also mentioned, which could place it under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the implementation of the control plane in Nimbus could place it under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
